.TH "tb_property_format_dir" 9 "tb_property_format_dir" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_property_format_dir \- Formats directory to the packed XDomain format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" tb_property_format_dir
.BI "(const struct tb_property_dir *dir "  ","
.BI "u32 *block "  ","
.BI "size_t block_len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dir" 12
Directory to format
.IP "block" 12
Property block where the packed data is placed
.IP "block_len" 12
Length of the property block
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function formats the directory to the packed format that can be
then send over the thunderbolt fabric to receiving host. Returns 0 in
case of success and negative errno on faulure. Passing NULL in \fIblock\fP
returns number of entries the block takes.
